{"questionId":"5275617","questionHtml":"<p>A standing wave with a first harmonic of frequency <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is formed on a string fixed at both ends.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/41e94b5e4de150d66d890c5a4082ff83bea1074f.png\"></p>\n<p>The frequency of the third harmonic is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>What is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; 3</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275617","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.17","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A standing wave with a first harmonic of frequency f1 is formed on a string fixed at both ends. The frequency of the third harmonic is f3. What is f1f3? A. 3 B. 32 C. 23 D. 13","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"17","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.1 – Simple harmonic motion","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}